  "prompt": "What does \"subject to availability\" mean?",
  "response": "\"Subject to availability\" means that something is only possible or will only happen if it is currently in stock, accessible, or has not already been reserved or taken by someone else. It indicates that the offer or item is not guaranteed and depends on whether it is still available at the time of request or purchase.\n\nFor example:\n- A hotel room might be \"subject to availability\"\n- A concert ticket might be \"subject to availability\"\n- A specific product or service might be \"subject to availability\"\n\nIn such cases, the customer cannot be certain they will get the item until it is confirmed as currently accessible.",
